Quantica Websocket API 1.0
  • application/json

This document describes the Quantica websocket APIs.

Servers

  • ws://localhost:6001socket.ioquantica-ws

Operations

  • PUB AxesUpdated

    Accepts the following message:

    WsGateway#emitAxesUpdated
    object
    uid: ResponseAxesDto
    required
    allOf

    X axis information

    object
    uid: Axis
    position
    required
    number

    Current axis position in micrometer

    isMoving
    required
    number

    If true, the axis is currently moving.

    Additional properties are allowed.

    required
    allOf

    Y axis information

    object
    uid: Axis
    position
    required
    number

    Current axis position in micrometer

    isMoving
    required
    number

    If true, the axis is currently moving.

    Additional properties are allowed.

    required
    allOf

    Z axis information

    object
    uid: Axis
    position
    required
    number

    Current axis position in micrometer

    isMoving
    required
    number

    Additional properties are allowed.

    Additional properties are allowed.

  },

  • PUB UpdatedPrinterSetting

    Accepts the following message:

    WsGateway#emitUpdatedPrinterSetting
    object
    uid: ResponsePrinterSettingDto
    id
    required
    number

    Id of the resource in the database.

    printerName
    required
    string

    Name of the printer.

    substrateOffsetMicrometer
    required
    number

    Height of a substrate laying on top of the print bed (i.e. plastic films, PCB's, etc.). This will adjust the z axis position during the print.

    heaterShutoffPeriodMs
    required
    number

    The heater will automatically turn of after the print finished if not used for this amount of time.

    printHeadOffsetMicrometer
    required
    deprecated
    number

    Deprecated, do not use. Print head offset in micrometer

    allOf

    Selected print bed that is being use while printing.

    object
    uid: ResponsePrintHeadProfileDto
    id
    required
    string

    Id of the firmware device.

    type
    required
    string

    Type of the print head.

      Allowed values:
    • "VOXLER24B"
    • "PADDLER48"
    • "PADDLER96"
    nozzleDistanceMicrometer
    required
    number

    Distance of the nozzles in micrometer.

    numberOfNozzles
    required
    number

    Number of nozzles of the print head.

    isSelected
    required
    boolean

    Flag if this profile is currently selected for printing.

    Additional properties are allowed.

    isPlanarizerRotationClockwise
    required
    boolean

    Flag for inverting the planarizer rotation.

    allOf

    Selected print bed that is being use while printing.

    object
    uid: ResponsePrintBedDto
    id
    required
    number

    Id of the resource in the database.

    sizeMicrometerX
    required
    number

    Print bed width in micrometers.

    sizeMicrometerY
    required
    number

    Print bed height in micrometers.

    startMicrometerX
    required
    number

    Start of the print bed relative to the encoder position.

    startMicrometerY
    required
    number

    Start of the print bed relative to the first print head nozzle.

    Additional properties are allowed.

    Additional properties are allowed.

    Examples

    {
  "id": 1,
  "printerName": "BB1-1",
  "substrateOffsetMicrometer": 104,
  "heaterShutoffPeriodMs": 300,
  "printHeadOffsetMicrometer": 0,
  "selectedPrintHeadProfile": {
    "id": "3979337D3430",
    "type": "PADDLER48",
    "nozzleDistanceMicrometer": 2200,
    "numberOfNozzles": 24,
    "isSelected": true
  },
  "isPlanarizerRotationClockwise": true,
  "selectedPrintBed": {
    "id": 1,
    "sizeMicrometerX": 204000,
    "sizeMicrometerY": 79200,
    "startMicrometerX": 3000,
    "startMicrometerY": 50800
  }
}
    This example has been generated automatically.

  • PUB UpdatedMaterialPumps

    This response is actually an array of objects

    Accepts the following message:

    WsGateway#emitUpdatedMaterialPumps
    object
    uid: ResponseMaterialPumpDto
    id
    required
    number

    Id of the resource in the database.

    deviceId
    required
    string

    Id of the firmware device.

    isActive
    required
    boolean

    State of the pump activation.

    intervalDurationMilliseconds
    required
    number

    Duration of the pumping while interval pumping is active in milliseconds

    intervalFrequencyVoxel
    required
    number

    Frequency interval that triggers the pumping after every n ejected voxels

    intervalFrequencyMs
    required
    number

    Time based interval for triggering pumping after every n milliseconds

    automaticPumping
    required
    string

    Type of the pump automation. TIME_BASED=Pumps every n milliseconds, VOXEL_BASED=Pumps every n ejected voxels, NONE=No automatic pumping

      Allowed values:
    • "OFF"
    • "TIME_BASED"
    • "VOXEL_BASED"

    Additional properties are allowed.

    Examples

    {
  "id": 1,
  "deviceId": "3979337D3430",
  "isActive": true,
  "intervalDurationMilliseconds": 1000,
  "intervalFrequencyVoxel": 50000,
  "intervalFrequencyMs": 60000,
  "automaticPumping": "TIME_BASED"
}
    This example has been generated automatically.

  • PUB UpdatedStaticTestModes

    This response is actually an array of objects

    Accepts the following message:

    WsGateway#emitUpdatedStaticTestModes
    object
    uid: ResponseStaticTestModeDto
    deviceId
    required
    string

    Id of the firmware device.

    activation
    required
    string

    Ejection activation mode of the static test. INTERNAL_TRIGGER: Ejection is triggered by the internal trigger of the print head. EXTERNAL_TRIGGER: Ejection is triggered by an external trigger signal. OFF: Ejection is deactivated.

      Allowed values:
    • "OFF"
    • "INTERNAL_TRIGGER"
    • "EXTERNAL_TRIGGER"
    ejection
    string

    Ejection type of the static test. BURST: Ejects in pulsing bursts with a firmware dependent amount of time between bursts. CONTINUOUS: Ejects the whole time.

      Allowed values:
    • "BURST"
    • "CONTINUOUS"

    Additional properties are allowed.

    Examples

    {
  "deviceId": "3979337D3430",
  "activation": "INTERNAL_TRIGGER",
  "ejection": "BURST"
}
    This example has been generated automatically.

  • PUB UpdatedFirmwareDevices

    This response is actually an array of objects

    Accepts the following message:

    WsGateway#emitUpdatedFirmwareDevices
    object
    uid: ResponseFirmwareDeviceDto
    id
    required
    string

    Id of the firmware device.

    version
    required
    string

    Currently flashed firmware version.

    type
    required
    string

    Type of the device.

      Allowed values:
    • "controlModule"
    • "printHeadModule"
    • "uvModule"
    • "unknown"
    connection
    required
    string

    Current connection of the device. NONE=Idle state while connection gets established, UNREACHABLE=The device is attached, but communication failed, CONNECTED=The device is attached and communication is open, DISCONNECTED=The device is attached, but communication is closed.

      Allowed values:
    • "NONE"
    • "UNREACHABLE"
    • "CONNECTED"
    • "DISCONNECTED"
    isVersionValid
    required
    boolean

    Check if the version is compatible with the printer software. The functionalities of this device is restricted to a minimum (e.g. only flashing).

    commit
    required
    string

    Commit number of the firmware running on the device.

    position
    number

    Slot position of the module. This is only relevant for modules, the control board has no position

    Additional properties are allowed.

    Examples

    {
  "id": "3979337D3430",
  "version": "1.0.0",
  "type": "printHeadModule",
  "connection": "CONNECTED",
  "isVersionValid": true,
  "commit": "562879c",
  "position": 0
}
    This example has been generated automatically.

  • PUB UpdatedActivePrint

    Accepts the following message:

    WsGateway#emitUpdatedActivePrint
    object
    uid: ResponsePrintDto
    id
    required
    number

    Id of the resource in the database.

    createdAt
    required
    string
    format: date-time

    Date the print was created.

    updatedAt
    required
    string
    format: date-time

    Date the print was last updated.

    state
    required
    string

    Current state of the print.

      Allowed values:
    • "STARTED"
    • "EXECUTE_SETUP"
    • "EXECUTE_INSTRUCTIONS"
    • "EXECUTE_TEARDOWN"
    • "STOPPED"
    • "FINISHED"
    • "FAILED"
    isActive
    required
    boolean

    Flag to indicate if the print is active.

    finishedAt
    string
    format: date-time

    Date the print was finished. Can be null if print is not finished.

    reportUploadUrl
    string

    URL the print report was uploaded to.

    currentLayer
    required
    number

    Current layer of the print.

    currentSweep
    required
    number

    Current sweep of the print within the layer.

    rawPrintTimeMs
    required
    number

    Total print time in milliseconds.

    required
    array<number>

    Number of sweeps per layer.

    Items:
    number
    required
    allOf

    Position offset in micrometers for each axis.

    object
    uid: ValuePerAxis
    X
    required
    number

    Value for X axis.

    Y
    required
    number

    Value for X axis.

    Z
    required
    number

    Value for X axis.

    Additional properties are allowed.

    required
    allOf

    Configuration used for the print.

    object
    uid: ResponsePrintConfigDto
    frequencyHz
    required
    number

    The shooting Frequency of the print head.

    nozzleSelection
    required
    string

    Strategy for defining which nozzles printing which line. This is being used in the print strategy. GREEDY=Nozzles are selected by maximum coverage. This can be fine-tuned by the minimumCoverage setting, RANDOM=Nozzles are selected randomly

      Allowed values:
    • "greedy"
    • "random"
    • "unknown"
    finishCuring
    required
    number

    Number of curing sweeps over each part of the object at the end of the print in order to fully cure the object.

    planarizerSpeed
    number

    Planarizer speed in rounds per minute.

    minimumCoverage
    required
    number

    Minimum number of nozzles that should print during a sweep. This value can fine-tune the strictness of the GREEDY print strategy.

    lineOrder
    required
    string

    Order of the lines laydown used in the print strategy. IN_ORDER=Lines are layed down side by side line by line, DIVIDE_AND_CONQUER=Lines are layed down in a divide and conquer fashion, PRIME_PERMUTATION=Lines are layed down in specified a prime permutation order, RANDOM=Lines are layed down randomly

      Allowed values:
    • "in_order"
    • "divide_and_conquer"
    • "prime_permutation"
    • "random"
    • "unknown"
    lineOrderRotation
    required
    boolean

    Flag for rotating the line order that is being used in the print strategy. This ensures that all overlapping layers are layed down differently in order to avoid layer lines.

    sweepDirection
    required
    string

    Sweep direction of the print.

      Allowed values:
    • "alternating"
    • "forward_only"
    • "backward_only"
    • "unknown"
    baseLayers
    required
    number

    Number of base layers that should get printed before starting with the solid layers.

    limitLayers
    required
    number

    Stop printing after this many layers. The print will finish after this amount of layers, you are not able to continue.

    layerMovementMicrometer
    required
    number

    Z axis movement in micrometers after each layer. This value cannot be lower than the layer height of the print.

    required
    allOf

    Settings for specifying curing that takes place at the start of the print head ejection during a sweep.

    object
    uid: CuringLaydownConfigDto
    required
    allOf

    Setting for the channel 0 of the uv module.

    object
    uid: CuringChannelConfigDto
    dutyCycle
    required
    number
    [ 0 .. 100 ]

    Duty cycle the uv module.

    highCurrent
    required
    boolean

    Value of the high current of the uv module.

    Additional properties are allowed.

    required
    allOf

    Setting for the channel 1 of the uv module.

    object
    uid: CuringChannelConfigDto
    dutyCycle
    required
    number
    [ 0 .. 100 ]

    Strategy for defining which nozzles printing which line. This is being used in the print strategy. GREEDY=Nozzles are selected by maximum coverage. This can be fine-tuned by the minimumCoverage setting, RANDOM=Nozzles are selected randomly

      Allowed values:
    • "greedy"
    • "random"
    • "unknown"

    required
    number

    required
    number

    Minimum number of nozzles that should print during a sweep. This value can fine-tune the strictness of the GREEDY print strategy.

    lineOrder
    required
    string

    Order of the lines laydown used in the print strategy. IN_ORDER=Lines are layed down side by side line by line, DIVIDE_AND_CONQUER=Lines are layed down in a divide and conquer fashion, PRIME_PERMUTATION=Lines are layed down in specified a prime permutation order, RANDOM=Lines are layed down randomly

      Allowed values:
    • "in_order"
    • "divide_and_conquer"
    • "prime_permutation"
    • "random"
    • "unknown"
